The [[First Lady of the United States]] is the hostess of the [[White House]]. The position is traditionally filled by the wife of the [[President of the United States]], with [[List of First Ladies of the United States|some historic exceptions]].
[[Helen Taft]] was the first First Lady to get her memoir published during her lifetime. Every memoir by a First Lady published in the 20th and 21st centuries has been a best seller, at times outselling those of their presidential husbands.<ref name=NYTIMES>{{citation |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2010/05/23/books/review/Fehrman-t.html |title=First Lady Lit |newspaper=[[The New York Times]] |first=Craig |last=Fehrman |date=May 21, 2010 |accessdate=March 30, 2015}}.</ref>
